# AI Security Enforcement

When creating or editing skills in this repo:

- **Trust Boundaries:** Every SKILL.md must include a Trust Boundaries section.
- **Output Validation:** Every SKILL.md must include an Output Validation section covering: validate recommendations before execution; highlight assumptions; identify uncertainty; require human review for high-risk actions; avoid unverifiable claims.
- **Tier 2:** Define safe vs unsafe actions; require validation checklist and user approval for unsafe.
- **Tier 3:** Require human review; high-risk outputs must include explicit warnings.
- **High-risk warnings:** Precede commands/patches with "This will execute/modify [X]. Confirm before proceeding."
- **AI-generated code:** Enforce human validation; no auto-apply without approval. Ensure traceability of AI-assisted changes.
- **Shadow AI:** Skills must not encourage unapproved AI tools; align with organizational AI stance.

Reference [docs/ai-security-model.md](docs/ai-security-model.md) for full model. See [docs/engineering-intelligence-framework.md](docs/engineering-intelligence-framework.md) for AI risk management.
